    "Ensemble Learning techniques, such as bagging, boosting and stacking, can further increase the predictive potential of the models by integrating their capabilities of various models Sagi and Rokach (2018).",
    "DNNs have been used with Ensemble Learning techniques include bagging and boosting in the research by Kostopoulos et al (2020) for the early prediction of students at risk of failure through extracting features from student data, and then using either bagging or boosting to combine the predictions of DNNs.",
    "This can help improve the accuracy of the predictions by reducing the variance of the individual models.",
    "Another method can be performed by combining DNNs with Random Forest (RF) as in Al-Zawqari et al (2022) or with K-means as in Kuo et al (2021); Yang et al (2022)).",
    "In Kuo et al (2021), courses were categorized using the K-means method based on the year and shared attributes, and then four layers of DNNs were applied for each year."
